snippet: Two explosions near the offices of Kurdish political parties were the deadliest of attacks that killed at least 40 people in northern Iraq, officials said.
abstract: Iraqi officials say assault in northern part of the country, with two bombs set off moments apart near offices of Kurdish political parties, is deadliest of series of attacks that have killed at least 40 people; nobody has claimed responsibility for attack, but militant group Islamic State in Iraq and Syria said it carried out previous bombings against Kurdish offices.
lead_paragraph: Two explosions near the offices of Kurdish political parties were the deadliest of attacks that killed at least 40 people in northern Iraq, officials said.
